TY  - JOUR
T1  - Factor-Market Rivalry
AU  - Markman, Gideon D.
AU  - Gianiodis, Peter T.
AU  - Buchholtz, Ann K.
Y1  - 2009/07/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.40632072
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2009.40632072
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 423
EP  - 441
VL  - 34
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - With its focus on product-market rivalry, competitive dynamics research fails to tell the whole story. We develop a theory of factor-market rivalry to shed light on atypical rivals and competitive blind spots. Focusing on resource versatility and mobility, the theory introduces dynamic constructs?resource discontinuities, leapfrogging, and captivity?and explains their role in triggering cascading effects. To illustrate the theory's conceptual utility, we apply the concepts of factor-market rivalry to mutual forbearance in multimarket competition.
AB  - With its focus on product-market rivalry, competitive dynamics research fails to tell the whole story. We develop a theory of factor-market rivalry to shed light on atypical rivals and competitive blind spots. Focusing on resource versatility and mobility, the theory introduces dynamic constructs?resource discontinuities, leapfrogging, and captivity?and explains their role in triggering cascading effects. To illustrate the theory's conceptual utility, we apply the concepts of factor-market rivalry to mutual forbearance in multimarket competition.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.40632072
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2009.40632072
Y2  - 2026/04/24
