T1  - An Interpretive Systems View of Knowledge Investments
AU  - Reus, Taco H.
AU  - Ranft, Annette L.
AU  - Lamont, Bruce T.
AU  - Adams, Garry L.
Y1  - 2009/07/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.40631556
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2009.40631556
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 382
EP  - 400
VL  - 34
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Viewing organizations as open, knowledge-dependent interpretation systems and building on the knowledge-based view, we develop a theoretical model of knowledge investments and value creation. By emphasizing the interpretive nature of organizations and examining knowledge requirements, capabilities, and investments, our contribution provides a more complete understanding of why some organizations make certain types of knowledge investments more than others and why these investments may have positive or negative effects on value creation.
AB  - Viewing organizations as open, knowledge-dependent interpretation systems and building on the knowledge-based view, we develop a theoretical model of knowledge investments and value creation. By emphasizing the interpretive nature of organizations and examining knowledge requirements, capabilities, and investments, our contribution provides a more complete understanding of why some organizations make certain types of knowledge investments more than others and why these investments may have positive or negative effects on value creation.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2009.40631556
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2009.40631556
